Heat oven to 425 degrees F. Spread sauce packet over crust. Meanwhile, heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat. Add sausage and onion. Cook 7 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until sausage is no longer pink and onion is tender. Drain. Top pizza with cooked sausage mixture, dollops of ricotta and Parmesan cheese. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until crust is golden brown.